<br>
Loot:<br>
<br>
Silk Gloves - Bank<br>
Plate Legs - Silound<br>
Plate Arms - Jakraak<br>
Plate Boots - Bangdang<br>
Plate Boots - Likes<br>
Leather Tunic - Lalyenea  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/nerd.gif ALT="8o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Leather Tunic - Keeni  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/nerd.gif ALT="8o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Plate Gauntlets x 3 - Bank<br>
Plate Legs - Ezmeer<br>
<br>
We also hit some named that were up and got the following:<br>
<br>
Emerald Symbol x 2<br>
Black Symbol<br>
Glowing Drake Orb<br>
<br>
Now there was some bitching about how we did the symbols.  Since this is our first time killing named we decided to guild bank the symbols for multiquest later.  The reason we did it this way is this.  Example: we had 4 symbols drop and 24 people were there, we random them and 4 different people have symbols, next time the same thing happens, however what are the chances that even one of the people who won last time will win again?  We would end up with various symbols scattered amongst everyone.  Instead the guild bank collects them.  Once we kill Dozekar we merit the tear to someone.  That person then gets to MQ the symbols out of the bank which means someone now has a fancy quest item, instead of that person sitting with a tear in the bank waiting to collect the rest of the symbols.<br>
<br>
Great raid last night, too bad the mobs got stingy after we had 2 leather tunics drop in a row.<br>
